# # 🚀 Playwright - Day 1 Notes (Beginner Friendly)

# ✅ STEP 1: Install Node.js
# Open Google
# Search: Node.js download
# Open official website
# Download LTS version
# Install it (Next → Next → Finish)
# Restart your system (recommended)

# ✅ STEP 2: Install VS Code (if not installed)
# Search: VS Code download
# Install it
# Open VS Code

# ✅ STEP 3: Open Project Folder
# Open VS Code
# Click File → Open Folder
# Create or select a folder (example: Playwright_Project)

# ✅ STEP 4: Open Terminal in VS Code
# Click: Terminal → New Terminal
# OR
# Press: Ctrl + `

# ✅ STEP 5: Install Playwright
# In terminal, type:
# 👉 npm init playwright@latest

# ✅ STEP 6: Select Options
# When prompted, choose:

# Language → JavaScript
# Add GitHub Actions → No
# Install Browsers → Yes

# 👉 Wait for installation to complete

# 📁 STEP 7: Check Project Files

# After installation, you will see:

# tests folder
# example.spec.js file
# playwright.config.js file

# ▶️ STEP 8: Run Your First Test
# In terminal, type:

# 👉 npx playwright test

# 🎯 That’s It for Day 1
# ✔ Playwright installed
# ✔ Project created
# ✔ Test executed